{"lemma":"ساكِنُو","slug":"ساكِنُو","root":"س.ك.ن","root_slug":"س-ك-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ن","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ساكِن","root":"سكن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20274"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%90%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inhabitant"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"stationary, motionless, still, unmoving"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unvowelled"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"placid"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to live together, to share quarters with (someone)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb سَكَنَ (sakana, “to live, to inhabit”)."},"ipa":["/saː.kin/","/saː.ka.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20274","headword_ar":"سَاكِنٌ","root":"skn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Still, motionless, stationary, in a state of rest, quiet, calm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unruffled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[applied to a letter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiescent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without a vowel immediately following it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"still, calm, tranquil, becoming appeased"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allayed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assuaged"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quelled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dying away, passing away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceasing to be: remitting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subsiding; becoming alleviated, light, slight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"still,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L. [See its verb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakana","text_ar":"سَكَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence.]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inhabiting, dwel-ling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding; an inhabitant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lodger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanN","text_ar":"سَكَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkinN","text_ar":"سَاكِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. thus used]: (L:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkinN","text_ar":"سَاكِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suk~aAnN","text_ar":"سُكَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo suk~aAnu fulaAnK","text_ar":"هُمْ سُكَّانُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are the lodgers of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suk~aAnu","text_ar":"سُكَّانُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAri","text_ar":"الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Genii, inhabiting the house."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L. [Respecting the custom of sacrificing an animal to the Jinn on the occasion of buying a house, in order to prevent any injury from the Jinn thereof, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ibojN","text_ar":"ذِبْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". The belief that houses are inhabited by Jinn obtains among the Arabs in the present day.]) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakonN","text_ar":"سَكْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  [Other meanings are indicated by explanations of its verb.]"}],"source_refs":["L","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}